~ statements are wrapped in parentheses — they read as asides, never as instructions.
~ conditionals reference already-defined static data only.

#book: { status - draft }

(if @book.status is draft)
@watermark Draft — do not distribute. watermark@
(end)

~ with else

#author: { corresponding - true, email - a.vane@coast.edu, name - Aldous Vane }

(if @author.corresponding is true)
Corresponding author: @author.email
(else)
@author.name
(end)

~ conditionals nest freely

#report: { status - final, audience - external }

(if @report.status is final)
(if @report.audience equals external)
@disclaimer Reviewed and approved for external circulation. disclaimer@
(else)
@disclaimer Final — internal only. disclaimer@
(end)
(end)
